<!-- MARKET CONTEXT -->
<div class="context">
  <h3>Market Context &amp; Key Themes — Q1 2026</h3>
  <div class="ctx-grid">
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>Mega-Deal Cycle Continues</strong>Power &amp; utility deal value hit $142B in 2025 (nearly 2× 2024 per PwC), carrying into Q1 2026. The AES take-private ($33.4B EV) is the largest clean energy infrastructure take-private of the current cycle, signaling aggressive private capital deployment into scale generation.</div>
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>Hyperscaler Vertical Integration</strong>Google's $4.75B Intersect close (Mar 12, 2026) and Amazon's $83M Oregon site win mark a structural shift: Big Tech is acquiring generating assets outright vs. relying on PPAs, driven by AI data center power demand and interconnection queues stretching 7–12 years.</div>
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>Offshore Wind Under Political Pressure</strong>TotalEnergies' $1B lease relinquishment (Attentive Energy + Carolina Long Bay, 4.2 GW combined, Mar 23, 2026) signals the practical shutdown of federal offshore wind support. Infrastructure funds should reassess offshore exposure and permitting timelines.</div>
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>OBBBA Reshaping Deal Flow</strong>The One Big Beautiful Bill Act tightened ITC/PTC qualification windows, compressing developer timelines and pushing acquirers toward deployment-ready, operating assets with secured interconnection. Greenfield M&amp;A now centers on acquiring queue positions and developer talent.</div>
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>Supply Chain M&amp;A Accelerates</strong>OBBBA domestic content requirements are driving industrial manufacturers into renewable supply chain acquisitions (MacLean-Fogg/OMCO Solar; GameChange/Terrasmart eBOS). US-manufactured components now directly affect ITC/PTC credit eligibility.</div>
    <div class="ctx-item"><strong>Scale as Competitive Moat</strong>Per PwC / Utility Dive: "scale will determine winners and losers." Renewable asset valuations have stabilized after 2024–25 compression — which analysts expect to unlock more seller activity in 2H 2026. Mid-tier players are seeking combinations to compete for data center power contracts.</div>
  </div>
</div>

